WEBVTT

00:05.207 --> 00:07.207
RALPH ANDERSON:
This guy has murdered a child.

00:07.875 --> 00:09.833
-(CAR TRUNK CREAKS)
-(BIKE SPINDLE CREAKS)

00:09.916 --> 00:12.041
We've got a slew of witnesses.

00:12.791 --> 00:14.916
Prints. DNA.

00:14.999 --> 00:16.166
(RADIO CHATTER)

00:16.416 --> 00:18.249
JOY PETERSON:
Did you kill my son?!

00:18.541 --> 00:20.541
HOWIE GOLD:
Is that not Terry Maitland...

00:21.333 --> 00:24.249
on the same day 70 miles away?

00:25.333 --> 00:26.207
Poof.

00:26.291 --> 00:27.333
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:27.708 --> 00:30.166
RALPH: Terry Maitland's prints
from the Sheraton prints,

00:30.249 --> 00:32.166
from the crime scene...
They all match.

00:32.249 --> 00:34.166
He can't have been
in two places at once.

00:34.249 --> 00:36.124
GOLD: We've got a video tape
and witnesses.

00:36.207 --> 00:38.124
What we've got beats
what they've got.

00:38.207 --> 00:42.333
If Terry Maitland is innocent,
we're not done.

00:44.666 --> 00:45.791
Jessa...

00:46.833 --> 00:47.666
No!

00:48.249 --> 00:51.374
He was here.
He was saying bad things to me.

00:51.458 --> 00:53.625
RALPH: It's like he's begging us
to catch him.

00:53.708 --> 00:55.541
What kind of criminal does that?

00:55.957 --> 00:59.124
Do you think Terry Maitland
killed that boy?

01:01.499 --> 01:03.124
RALPH: I really don't know.

01:10.291 --> 01:12.124
-♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪
-(RAIN FALLING)

01:17.124 --> 01:19.458
(GATE SQUEAKING)

01:33.333 --> 01:34.583
ROBERTO BEAN:
Kinda late for a visit.

01:34.666 --> 01:35.625
(CAR LOCKS)

01:35.708 --> 01:37.291
RALPH ANDERSON:
Oh, it's not a social call.

01:41.583 --> 01:42.666
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

01:45.041 --> 01:46.124
(DOOR CLOSES)

02:03.124 --> 02:04.916
(METAL DETECTOR WHIRRS)

02:10.374 --> 02:13.041
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:23.082 --> 02:24.916
(GATE CREEKS OPEN)

02:29.708 --> 02:31.833
(GATE RATTLING)

02:34.207 --> 02:35.833
(KEYS JANGLING)

02:46.291 --> 02:47.957
(GATE RATTLING)

02:51.916 --> 02:52.916
(DOOR OPENS)

02:59.166 --> 03:00.708
RALPH: Can we lose the cuffs?

03:00.791 --> 03:01.750
ROBERTO: Against protocol.

03:01.833 --> 03:03.249
I'll take
responsibility for him.

03:03.333 --> 03:04.708
ROBERTO: No, sir, you won't.

03:11.291 --> 03:12.374
(DOOR SLAMS)

03:17.416 --> 03:18.583
Howie Saloman...

03:18.666 --> 03:20.082
would probably
fire me as a client

03:20.166 --> 03:21.583
if he knew I was talking to you.

03:24.082 --> 03:25.750
Well, it's the same on my end.

03:27.916 --> 03:30.333
You have any idea what
the D.A. would do to me?

03:32.791 --> 03:34.291
TERRY MAITLAND:
Tell me why you're here.

03:36.625 --> 03:37.625
Um...

03:42.041 --> 03:44.916
The van with the New York plates
is still...

03:44.999 --> 03:46.124
troubling me.

03:48.124 --> 03:51.583
TERRY: Mm-hm, the van I've
never seen before in my life?

03:51.666 --> 03:54.416
The last time I was in New York
was 16 years ago,

03:54.499 --> 03:55.791
for my honeymoon.

03:57.791 --> 03:59.999
Oh. I didn't know that.

04:02.374 --> 04:04.750
I mean, I knew you hadn't been
there recently.

04:06.999 --> 04:09.458
We, of course,
back checked your movements

04:09.541 --> 04:10.957
over the last six months.

04:12.791 --> 04:14.333
Couldn't find anything
but a...

04:15.875 --> 04:16.999
family vacation

04:17.499 --> 04:18.957
to, uh, Dayton.

04:20.166 --> 04:21.916
And we flew
both directions for that,

04:21.999 --> 04:23.207
as I'm sure you know.

04:30.583 --> 04:31.666
I'm as baffled...

04:33.249 --> 04:35.499
by this conflicting evidence
as you are.

04:37.499 --> 04:38.916
Um...

04:38.999 --> 04:40.625
Hey, will you tell me
why you're here?

04:42.916 --> 04:44.082
That...

04:44.166 --> 04:46.541
(CLEARS THROAT) TV footage...

04:47.666 --> 04:50.875
puts you at the
teachers' conference in Cap City

04:50.957 --> 04:53.082
at the same time as
Frankie Peterson's murder

04:53.166 --> 04:54.499
sixty miles away.

04:55.499 --> 04:57.625
But I have
credible witnesses...

04:57.708 --> 05:00.333
credible witnesses who saw you

05:00.416 --> 05:02.957
walking around covered in
Frankie Peterson's blood.

05:03.041 --> 05:04.875
Your prints are
all over the van,

05:05.291 --> 05:06.374
the crime scene,

05:07.291 --> 05:08.333
the boy.

05:13.374 --> 05:14.791
Want me to explain
all that to you?

05:14.875 --> 05:15.791
-No.
-Good.

05:15.875 --> 05:17.416
-Because you can't?
-Right.

05:17.499 --> 05:19.166
Right? And no one can.

05:22.416 --> 05:27.583
On March 30th, 2019,
did you have any physical...

05:28.708 --> 05:31.875
or verbal contact
with Frankie Peterson?

05:35.625 --> 05:36.625
Nope.

05:41.583 --> 05:45.499
On March 30th, 2019,
did you abduct Frankie Peterson?

05:45.583 --> 05:46.666
No.

05:46.750 --> 05:50.249
On March 30th, 2019,
did you murder Frankie Peterson?

05:53.249 --> 05:54.957
I didn't kill that kid, Ralph.

06:02.708 --> 06:03.750
That it?

06:05.207 --> 06:06.374
For tonight, yeah.

06:06.458 --> 06:07.999
-Okay.
-Thank you.

06:08.082 --> 06:08.999
(RALPH SIGHS)

06:09.082 --> 06:10.708
You know, Ralph,
when you arrested me...

06:11.750 --> 06:13.249
in front of all those people...

06:14.416 --> 06:15.625
at that game...

06:17.499 --> 06:19.916
you asked me if I'd
ever touched your son, Derek.

06:19.999 --> 06:21.124
Do you remember that?

06:23.708 --> 06:26.333
Be very careful about
what you say to me next.

06:35.374 --> 06:38.082
In all the years I've been
coaching Little League...

06:38.166 --> 06:40.499
your son, Derek,
was the best drag bunter...

06:40.957 --> 06:41.957
I ever had.

06:42.875 --> 06:44.124
And he was just a little guy,

06:44.207 --> 06:46.833
you know, he was very small,
smallest kid on the team,

06:47.583 --> 06:48.666
but he had a lot of guts,

06:48.750 --> 06:50.082
he was never afraid to
crowd the plate,

06:50.166 --> 06:52.750
even if there was some great,
big eighth-grader throwing heat.

06:54.333 --> 06:57.458
In most kids that short
you just count on 'em for walks.

06:57.541 --> 06:59.625
That's all you can expect,
but he wasn't havin' that,

06:59.708 --> 07:02.166
he just kept swinging,
and striking out,

07:02.249 --> 07:04.291
and the kids
even started calling him...

07:04.833 --> 07:06.374
uh, the "Whiffer."

07:06.458 --> 07:08.333
Secretly,
they called him Whiffer.

07:08.416 --> 07:11.124
I asked them to stop,
but they're 12 and 11...

07:11.207 --> 07:13.999
Only time he got on base was
when he got hit by a pitch, so,

07:14.791 --> 07:15.791
tough to blame 'em.

07:15.875 --> 07:17.750
But when I saw that
he wasn't gonna quit,

07:17.833 --> 07:20.957
that he was gonna just
keep swingin' and striking out,

07:21.041 --> 07:23.291
I taught him how to bunt,

07:24.625 --> 07:27.291
and not a lot of kids
like to do that.

07:27.374 --> 07:29.499
They're afraid they'd drop that
bat over the plate,

07:29.583 --> 07:31.750
fast ball comes in,
they get their fingers smashed,

07:31.833 --> 07:33.416
but not him.

07:33.499 --> 07:35.541
He never flinched,
not once.

07:35.625 --> 07:36.916
And he flew down
that first base line,

07:36.999 --> 07:39.082
and you remember how many
bunt singles he got?

07:39.166 --> 07:40.541
A lot more than I expected.

07:41.916 --> 07:43.458
But those kids stopped
calling him Whiffer,

07:43.541 --> 07:45.207
and they started
calling him "Push It."

07:47.124 --> 07:48.875
Right? He'd come up to the plate

07:48.957 --> 07:50.999
runners on the corners,
they'd start saying,

07:51.082 --> 07:53.082
"Push it, Derek, push it."

07:53.166 --> 07:56.166
So he had a new handle that year
when we almost won district.

07:58.041 --> 08:00.791
You must have noticed
a difference in him, right?

08:00.875 --> 08:02.249
Did you notice that that summer?

08:02.333 --> 08:03.583
How confident he was?

08:07.166 --> 08:08.124
How proud he was?

08:08.207 --> 08:10.374
He was a--
He was a big little guy.

08:11.458 --> 08:13.249
And, um, you know,
I don't want--

08:13.333 --> 08:15.458
I don't want you
to get the wrong impression;

08:15.541 --> 08:17.416
he practiced, a lot,

08:18.207 --> 08:19.374
but I taught him that.

08:20.583 --> 08:21.791
I taught him how to bunt.

08:24.583 --> 08:26.875
So, when you asked me if I ever
touched your kid...

08:36.416 --> 08:37.583
I really hope I did.

08:44.957 --> 08:46.041
(HANDCUFFS RATTLE)

08:50.916 --> 08:51.999
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

08:52.082 --> 08:53.333
CRAIG KOHARA:
Personally, I'm partial

08:53.416 --> 08:54.916
to the Presidential;

08:54.999 --> 08:57.583
solid mahogany with
a high gloss finish,

08:58.458 --> 09:01.249
or anything with
the velvet interior,

09:01.333 --> 09:04.166
and the classic French Fold
design

09:04.249 --> 09:05.999
with a hinged spilt couch,

09:06.082 --> 09:08.124
and the adjustable
eternal rest bed.

09:08.207 --> 09:09.499
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

09:09.583 --> 09:10.791
And since you
will be ordering two

09:10.875 --> 09:13.499
I'd be willing to offer you
a 20 percent discount

09:13.583 --> 09:14.791
on the embalming.

09:17.583 --> 09:19.416
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

09:24.625 --> 09:26.374
REPORTER 1: In my 18 years
as a reporter

09:26.458 --> 09:27.583
here at Cherokee City, Bill,

09:27.666 --> 09:30.541
we've never had a case
as high profile as this one.

09:30.625 --> 09:33.833
We have all the reporters,
all of the law enforcement here,

09:33.916 --> 09:35.374
and plenty of passionate locals

09:35.458 --> 09:37.957
who really just wanna get
a glimpse of Terry Maitland.

09:38.041 --> 09:40.207
He, of course,
is the accused child killer,

09:40.291 --> 09:43.249
and he should be making a court
appearance here momentarily.

09:43.333 --> 09:44.833
REPORTER 2: Most of them
would like to see

09:44.916 --> 09:47.333
justice against accused killer
Terry Maitland,

09:47.416 --> 09:49.541
but others are here to offer
their support.

09:49.625 --> 09:52.916
And this is the direct result
of that bombshell footage

09:52.999 --> 09:56.166
that was leaked online
last night, of Maitland.

09:56.249 --> 09:59.249
He's caught on tape attending
a literary convention

09:59.333 --> 10:02.458
at the same time
Frankie Peterson was murdered.

10:02.541 --> 10:04.374
D.A. Hayes,
do you worry your focus

10:04.458 --> 10:05.791
is so narrow on Terry Maitland

10:05.875 --> 10:09.249
that you could be letting other
potential suspects pass by?

10:09.333 --> 10:10.583
No, absolutely not.

10:10.666 --> 10:12.333
I have no doubt in my mind that
the man we have in custody

10:12.416 --> 10:14.541
is the man who murdered
Frankie Peterson

10:14.625 --> 10:15.999
on the afternoon of
March the 30th.

10:16.082 --> 10:18.249
And on a personal note,
are the rumors true?

10:18.333 --> 10:21.333
Could we actually see your name
on the ballot next March?

10:21.416 --> 10:22.875
D.A. KENNETH HAYES:
All I care about today

10:22.957 --> 10:25.416
is securing justice for the kid
who was brutally killed

10:25.499 --> 10:26.916
while walking home
in a neighborhood

10:26.999 --> 10:28.957
we allowed him to think
was safe.

10:29.041 --> 10:30.541
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

10:36.541 --> 10:39.041
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(CAMERA CLICKING)

10:40.957 --> 10:42.583
♪ (EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

10:49.416 --> 10:52.499
(CROWD BOOING)

10:54.374 --> 10:55.666
OFFICER: Okay, we're good.

10:56.708 --> 10:57.916
(CROWD BOOING)

10:57.999 --> 10:59.458
(CAMERAS CLICKING)

10:59.541 --> 11:01.750
(CROWD BOOING)

11:02.416 --> 11:05.041
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

11:05.541 --> 11:07.416
(CROWD CLAMORS)

11:07.750 --> 11:08.750
Okay.

11:13.583 --> 11:15.875
(CROWD YELLING)

11:15.957 --> 11:17.082
MAN: Killer!

11:23.416 --> 11:24.541
MAN 2: Die, asshole!

11:24.625 --> 11:26.291
MAN 3: Disgusting!
You degenerate!

11:35.291 --> 11:37.541
(CROWD SCREAMING)

11:40.249 --> 11:42.416
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

12:06.916 --> 12:08.333
(CAR TIRES SCREECH)

12:08.416 --> 12:10.291
(CROWD SCREAMING)

12:17.416 --> 12:18.458
Terry.

12:19.124 --> 12:21.041
Terry, Terry.

12:21.124 --> 12:23.416
Terry, let me see.
Let me see, let me see.

12:23.499 --> 12:24.875
-(TERRY GROANS IN PAIN)
-GLORY: Oh!

12:24.957 --> 12:27.124
HOWARD SALOMAN: Oh, Jesus. 911!

12:27.207 --> 12:29.291
-HOWARD: No! 911!
-GLORY: Terry. Hey, Terry.

12:30.666 --> 12:32.999
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

12:40.124 --> 12:41.333
HOWARD: Call 911!

12:43.791 --> 12:44.750
GLORY: Hey.

12:44.833 --> 12:46.166
(TERRY GRUNTS)

12:46.249 --> 12:47.541
GLORY: Hey, breathe with me.

12:47.625 --> 12:49.249
-RALPH: Hey. Let me take a look.
-GLORY: Breathe with me.

12:49.333 --> 12:50.875
RALPH: Let me take a look,
let me take a look.

12:50.957 --> 12:52.082
Let me take a look. No...

12:52.166 --> 12:53.791
-GLORY: Oh, God.
-RALPH: Okay, come here.

12:53.875 --> 12:55.291
Put your hand there.
Just keep it there.

12:55.374 --> 12:56.666
Right there, right there.

12:56.750 --> 12:58.583
-(TERRY CHOKING)
-Look at me, Terry. Terry.

12:58.666 --> 13:00.708
(GASPS) I didn't do it.

13:02.166 --> 13:04.499
-TERRY: I wasn't there.
-(GLORY WHIMPERS)

13:04.583 --> 13:05.833
TERRY: It wasn't me.

13:06.750 --> 13:07.875
It wasn't me.

13:09.916 --> 13:10.791
(TERRY CHOKES)

13:10.875 --> 13:12.249
Jus-- Just, Terry,
keep looking at me.

13:12.333 --> 13:13.875
-Keep looking at me.
-HOWARD: Terry.

13:13.957 --> 13:15.791
Ralph, we have a doctor here.

13:15.875 --> 13:17.541
Hey, Terry,
stay with me, please.

13:17.625 --> 13:19.041
-GLORY: It's okay.
-DOCTOR: Hey, I'm a doctor.

13:19.124 --> 13:20.291
-I'm here to help, okay?
-(TERRY GURGLES)

13:20.374 --> 13:21.833
DOCTOR: We're gonna help you,
buddy. Stay with us.

13:21.916 --> 13:24.041
-(TERRY GURGLING)
-DOCTOR: Stay with us, buddy.

13:24.124 --> 13:26.499
DOCTOR: Got the bleeding under
control. Did someone call 911?

13:26.583 --> 13:27.833
HOWARD: Yes.

13:29.291 --> 13:31.458
(INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER
POLICE RADIO)

13:31.541 --> 13:32.957
DOCTOR: Can you tell me
your name, buddy?

13:33.041 --> 13:34.207
-What's his name?
-It's Terry.

13:34.291 --> 13:36.458
DOCTOR: Terry. Come on, Terry,
stay with us, okay?

13:36.541 --> 13:38.249
-I need you to breathe.
-HOWARD: Terry.

13:38.333 --> 13:39.625
DOCTOR: Terry,
can you talk to me?

13:39.708 --> 13:40.625
HOWARD: Terry.

13:40.708 --> 13:41.833
DOCTOR: Come on, Terry,
stay with us.

13:41.916 --> 13:42.999
We have more help coming
on the way.

13:43.082 --> 13:44.583
We're gonna get you
to the hospital, okay?

13:45.625 --> 13:47.541
DOCTOR: Come on, Terry,
stay with us.

13:55.291 --> 13:58.916
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

14:08.916 --> 14:11.207
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

14:13.499 --> 14:15.082
-(DOOR SQUEAKS)
-(BEEPING)

14:16.249 --> 14:17.625
MYRON LAZAR: Hello, sir.

14:18.583 --> 14:19.625
Any complaints?

14:20.249 --> 14:21.249
RALPH: Um...

14:23.333 --> 14:24.541
I killed a boy.

14:26.291 --> 14:27.416
Um...

14:27.499 --> 14:28.708
MYRON: I meant your body.

14:29.249 --> 14:30.291
Does anything hurt?

14:31.249 --> 14:32.291
RALPH: No, it's just...

14:33.249 --> 14:34.291
tight all over.

14:36.291 --> 14:38.166
MYRON: Any medical history
I should know about?

14:41.124 --> 14:42.916
RALPH: Uh, um, no, no.

14:47.791 --> 14:48.999
MYRON: You on any medications?

14:52.041 --> 14:53.541
RALPH: Lipitor...

14:53.625 --> 14:54.791
for cholesterol.

14:56.207 --> 14:58.750
MYRON: Are there any other drugs
in your system right now?

14:58.833 --> 15:00.124
RALPH: No, sir.

15:05.082 --> 15:06.166
MYRON: Okay.

15:06.249 --> 15:07.957
(VELCRO SCRATCHES)

15:08.041 --> 15:11.666
Well, I'm a little concerned
about your elevated BP so...

15:13.583 --> 15:15.499
what I'd like to do right now

15:15.583 --> 15:18.041
is to pull this curtain here,
and turn off the lights.

15:19.082 --> 15:20.916
Just lay back, close your eyes,

15:20.999 --> 15:22.583
and concentrate
on your breathing.

15:22.666 --> 15:25.041
Let's see if we can get it down
on its own, okay?

15:28.541 --> 15:29.625
RALPH: Yeah.

15:30.291 --> 15:32.082
(TROLLEY JINGLING)

15:32.166 --> 15:34.416
DETECTIVE: I'm sorry
for your loss, Mrs. Maitland.

15:34.499 --> 15:35.458
♪ (SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

15:35.541 --> 15:37.333
I just need you to answer
a few questions

15:37.416 --> 15:39.541
while things are still fresh
in your mind.

15:39.625 --> 15:40.916
Would that be all right
with you?

15:40.999 --> 15:42.583
(GLORY EXHALES DEEPLY)

15:42.666 --> 15:43.666
(SNIFFS)

15:43.750 --> 15:44.833
Yes.

15:52.082 --> 15:54.333
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

16:21.875 --> 16:23.207
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

16:38.499 --> 16:39.583
(CELL PHONE ALERT)

16:40.207 --> 16:42.041
(BOAR GRUNTS)

16:45.124 --> 16:46.541
Mother fuck!

16:55.499 --> 16:56.750
Son of a bitch!

16:59.916 --> 17:01.957
-(DOOR SLAMS)
-(TIRES SCREECH)

17:08.750 --> 17:11.416
(FLIES BUZZING)

17:17.583 --> 17:18.625
(DOORBELL RINGS)

17:27.957 --> 17:29.041
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

17:29.124 --> 17:31.082
-(DOOR SQUEAKS OPEN)
-YUNIS SABLO: Hi, Mrs. Anderson.

17:31.166 --> 17:33.499
(YUNIS CONTINUES SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY)

17:37.957 --> 17:38.999
(DOOR CLOSES)

17:42.207 --> 17:43.458
Evening, Lieutenant.

17:44.082 --> 17:45.124
YUNIS: Hey.

17:46.583 --> 17:47.791
How you holding up?

17:48.207 --> 17:49.791
(RALPH GRUNTS)

17:49.875 --> 17:51.458
You're on administrative leave?

17:54.291 --> 17:56.583
Yep, two weeks.

17:56.666 --> 17:59.833
They've ordered me to
see a, uh, trauma therapist.

18:01.625 --> 18:02.666
You should.

18:04.458 --> 18:06.249
When do I get my gun back?

18:06.333 --> 18:08.166
Let's see what the therapist
says first.

18:12.833 --> 18:14.041
How's Tamika doing?

18:15.041 --> 18:16.207
YUNIS: She's laid up.

18:16.291 --> 18:19.666
Cherokee Springs Medical Center,
with a shattered tibia.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.666
She's mostly worried
about the baby.

18:22.833 --> 18:24.583
She should never have been at
the courthouse,

18:24.666 --> 18:25.833
I don't know why I...

18:27.791 --> 18:28.791
(SIGHS)

18:28.875 --> 18:30.249
That's my call.

18:30.333 --> 18:32.999
