and how it doesn't add up, and--

35:49.708 --> 35:51.666
-You go see that shrink yet?
-No, I haven't.

35:52.499 --> 35:54.374
Look,
the Maitlands were in Dayton

35:54.458 --> 35:57.041
from March 3rd to March 7th.

35:57.124 --> 36:01.625
Now, if our guy dropped that van
at any time during those days,

36:01.708 --> 36:05.625
and if they even came close
to crossing paths,

36:05.708 --> 36:08.082
we would wanna know about that,
right?

36:09.082 --> 36:10.499
-Right?
-♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

36:10.583 --> 36:12.750
RALPH: Is the kid still
locked up in Chattanooga?

36:12.833 --> 36:14.374
YUNIS: He's not locked up.

36:14.458 --> 36:16.374
Cop who made the collar
took a liking to him,

36:16.458 --> 36:18.333
put him in foster care.

36:18.416 --> 36:20.041
Kid running from a violent home;

36:20.124 --> 36:21.291
nobody wants
to see him get hurt.

36:21.374 --> 36:23.041
-I wanna talk to him.
-YUNIS: Why?

36:23.124 --> 36:24.999
He already said he doesn't
remember where he was.

36:25.082 --> 36:26.333
Okay, great.

36:26.416 --> 36:29.124
So now can-- can you just reach
out to somebody up there please,

36:29.207 --> 36:30.541
and make it happen?

36:32.041 --> 36:33.999
I'll make a deal with you,
Ralph.

36:34.082 --> 36:35.916
You do something for me...

36:36.708 --> 36:38.625
and I'll drive you
up there myself.

36:42.499 --> 36:44.249
HERBERT ZUCKER: Have you
been to a therapist before,

36:44.333 --> 36:45.541
Detective Anderson?

36:45.625 --> 36:47.333
Um...

36:47.416 --> 36:49.833
We saw a grief counselor
in Atlanta...

36:49.957 --> 36:51.791
after my son died.

36:52.291 --> 36:53.166
(SNIFFS)

36:53.249 --> 36:54.458
Sorry to hear that.

36:55.041 --> 36:56.124
How old was he?

36:56.207 --> 36:57.833
I'm not here to talk about him.

37:01.041 --> 37:02.207
Was he helpful?

37:02.291 --> 37:03.374
RALPH: She.

37:03.458 --> 37:04.625
Was she helpful?

37:04.708 --> 37:06.625
Well, I'm still grieving, so...

37:09.458 --> 37:10.833
She was okay, it was okay.

37:12.750 --> 37:13.957
(RALPH CLEARS THROAT)

37:15.166 --> 37:16.416
How are you feeling today?

37:17.916 --> 37:19.124
How do you think I'm feeling?

37:25.875 --> 37:28.124
Sorrowful, angry...

37:30.833 --> 37:32.957
-Getting any sleep?
-Not much.

37:34.916 --> 37:35.957
Dreams?

37:37.666 --> 37:38.957
We're at dreams already?

37:41.291 --> 37:42.499
Well...

37:42.583 --> 37:43.666
If you ask ten therapists

37:43.750 --> 37:45.499
for the best way to open
with a new patient

37:45.583 --> 37:47.124
you'll get
ten different answers.

37:50.124 --> 37:51.666
Yeah, I'm having some dreams.

37:53.875 --> 37:55.333
Can you describe those?

37:56.999 --> 37:58.082
Uh, yeah.

37:58.166 --> 38:00.499
People runnin', people shoutin',
people getting hurt,

38:00.583 --> 38:03.124
people getting shot, um, but...

38:04.499 --> 38:06.374
they're kinda slow motion
a little bit,

38:06.458 --> 38:07.833
and the sound is
a little bit strange.

38:07.916 --> 38:10.625
It's basically the same thing
that happened on the day.

38:10.708 --> 38:12.166
Exactly as it was.

38:12.249 --> 38:13.249
(SNIFFS)

38:13.333 --> 38:14.458
(CLEARS THROAT)

38:14.541 --> 38:15.666
In these dreams,

38:15.750 --> 38:18.374
were there any specific details
that stuck with you?

38:19.708 --> 38:21.750
♪ (SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

38:30.124 --> 38:31.166
No.

38:33.708 --> 38:34.750
Detective...

38:38.541 --> 38:41.666
let me just give you
the big picture going forward.

38:41.750 --> 38:44.207
It's good you came in
so soon after what happened,

38:45.374 --> 38:46.957
but the potential injuries
to your psyche,

38:47.041 --> 38:49.333
those can take weeks,
or months...

38:49.416 --> 38:50.416
(RALPH SIGHS)

38:50.499 --> 38:52.291
...even longer
to announce themselves so I--

38:52.374 --> 38:53.708
RALPH: Yeah, but doctor...

38:53.791 --> 38:54.875
you know what?

38:55.791 --> 38:57.833
The so called "reason" I'm here

38:57.916 --> 38:59.999
is that the shooting has made me
so crazy

39:00.082 --> 39:02.291
-I can't go back to work--
-Crazy's a meaningless word.

39:02.374 --> 39:03.374
Whatever.

39:03.458 --> 39:05.750
Look, I've been
a law enforcement professional

39:05.833 --> 39:07.374
for over 20 years.

39:07.458 --> 39:11.458
So, is it even imaginable
to you that I'm fine?

39:12.499 --> 39:13.791
HERBERT: Do you feel fine?

39:13.875 --> 39:15.291
Fuck no, I don't feel fine

39:15.374 --> 39:17.957
but that's not really the--
the point.

39:18.041 --> 39:21.666
Look, being here is just more
like a punishment,

39:21.750 --> 39:23.124
feels more like that.

39:27.166 --> 39:29.458
If you wanna walk out, Ralph,
I'm not gonna stop you.

39:36.916 --> 39:39.291
It's just that when anybody says
to me,

39:39.374 --> 39:40.999
"I'm here to help,"

39:41.082 --> 39:42.957
things invariably get worse.

39:47.249 --> 39:49.166
(CAR DOORS CLOSES)

39:49.999 --> 39:51.291
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

39:51.374 --> 39:53.625
-(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)
-(BIRD CAWING)

39:55.416 --> 39:58.166
(CHILDREN PLAYING IN DISTANCE)

40:01.791 --> 40:03.625
-(CHILDREN PLAYING)
-(DOG BARKING)

40:07.625 --> 40:09.416
-GIRL: Snap!
-GIRL 2: I want all of them.

40:09.499 --> 40:11.374
GIRL 3: Why don't we just
take turns?

40:11.458 --> 40:14.166
-(CHILDREN PLAYING)
-GIRL 4: Yeah! Lego bus?

40:16.499 --> 40:18.499
GIRL 5: So, first we decide on
the rules we play...

40:18.583 --> 40:19.666
I'll be right here.

40:21.333 --> 40:22.541
RALPH: Hey, Merlin.

40:23.333 --> 40:24.708
Hey there, I'm Ralph.

40:25.333 --> 40:27.124
This is Yunis.

40:27.207 --> 40:29.791
We just, um,
wanted to ask you, uh,

40:29.875 --> 40:32.666
some questions about some of
these photographs we have.

40:32.750 --> 40:33.957
Do you, um...

40:34.666 --> 40:35.999
Do you recognize this?

40:38.583 --> 40:39.625
It's a restaurant.

40:39.708 --> 40:42.999
Uh, yeah, that's right.
It's, uh, it's in Dayton,

40:43.750 --> 40:45.833
and, um...
(CLEARS THROAT)

40:45.916 --> 40:46.999
...we found this...

40:47.791 --> 40:50.082
in the, um, in the van

40:50.166 --> 40:53.207
that you, uh, that you drove
down from New York,

40:53.291 --> 40:55.957
and so one of the things that
I'm hoping to achieve today,

40:56.041 --> 40:58.750
with your help, son,
is to, uh,

40:58.833 --> 41:03.249
is to pin down exactly where
you might have left that van.

41:03.333 --> 41:04.875
So, um...

41:04.957 --> 41:07.791
W-- Would you like to sit down,
and talk to us about it?

41:07.875 --> 41:09.875
MERLIN CASSIDY: I've never seen
this restaurant before.

41:10.416 --> 41:12.041
Okay.

41:12.124 --> 41:14.957
Why don't you take a look at
this photograph and...

41:15.041 --> 41:16.625
just take your time.

41:16.708 --> 41:17.875
Take your time.

41:20.499 --> 41:22.708
Yeah, I was in this parking lot.

41:23.625 --> 41:25.957
This baseball card store,

41:26.041 --> 41:29.166
I wanted to go in but I was
too nervous to hang around.

41:29.249 --> 41:31.124
You like baseball, Merlin?

41:31.207 --> 41:32.291
I like the cards.

41:32.374 --> 41:34.750
We're trying to make
an Astros fan out of him.

41:35.625 --> 41:36.791
And when was this?

41:36.875 --> 41:38.875
(MERLIN CLICKS TONGUE AND SIGHS)

41:40.458 --> 41:41.708
Three cars ago.

41:42.333 --> 41:43.666
RALPH: Okay, um...

41:43.750 --> 41:46.708
well what-- what we're hoping
to do here is, um,

41:46.791 --> 41:50.499
to maybe narrow it down
to the day, or even the week,

41:50.583 --> 41:51.875
um, do you wanna sit down?

41:51.957 --> 41:53.916
You wanna-- You sure you don't
wanna sit down and talk to us?

41:54.249 --> 41:55.374
I'm okay.

41:55.458 --> 41:58.583
Okay, so when you were driving
did you, um...

41:58.666 --> 42:00.625
-did you listen to the radio?
-MERLIN: No.

42:02.041 --> 42:03.750
Did you...

42:03.833 --> 42:05.625
notice anything like, um,

42:05.708 --> 42:07.916
a date and time display
out the front of a bank,

42:07.999 --> 42:09.416
or a gas station?

42:10.750 --> 42:13.625
Maybe you went into
a convenience store,

42:13.708 --> 42:16.166
and saw a headline
on a newspaper,

42:16.249 --> 42:19.416
or a magazine cover,
or the TV was on?

42:19.499 --> 42:21.791
A TV in a 7-Eleven.

42:21.875 --> 42:24.916
The lady behind the counter,
she had a little one running.

42:28.082 --> 42:30.791
She had this big smudge
on her forehead.

42:32.082 --> 42:33.625
I thought it was weird 'cause...

42:33.708 --> 42:35.458
she was taking people's money
all day,

42:35.541 --> 42:37.082
and not bothering
to clean her face.

42:37.166 --> 42:39.875
-RALPH: Mm-hm.
-Was it a smudge like this?

42:39.957 --> 42:42.041
Yeah, it was kinda like an X.

42:42.124 --> 42:45.625
Did you see anybody else that
day with something like that?

42:46.708 --> 42:48.625
There was a guy
in the parking lot,

42:49.041 --> 42:50.374
he had it too...

42:50.458 --> 42:52.416
and a girl,

42:52.499 --> 42:54.791
about my age,
coming out of a McDonald's...

42:55.374 --> 42:56.750
Maybe it was a KFC.

43:04.583 --> 43:06.625
The Ash Wednesday
fell on March 6th,

43:07.916 --> 43:09.458
and the Maitlands were in Dayton

43:09.541 --> 43:11.916
from March 3rd to March 7th.

43:11.999 --> 43:13.333
YUNIS: But they flew both ways.

43:14.249 --> 43:15.625
Terry was on that flight?

43:17.999 --> 43:20.416
(BIRDS CAWING)

43:20.499 --> 43:22.541
-Yeah.
-(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

43:33.833 --> 43:35.374
(DRAWER OPENS)

43:35.458 --> 43:37.041
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

43:39.499 --> 43:40.750
(GLORY SIGHS)

43:40.833 --> 43:41.875
(DRAWER CLOSES)

43:44.750 --> 43:45.875
(DOOR SQUEAKS)

43:47.041 --> 43:48.166
(DOOR CREAKS)

43:51.875 --> 43:53.916
-(GLORY SIGHS)
-(GATE SQUEAKING)

43:53.999 --> 43:56.291
-RALPH: Glory.
-GLORY: No.

43:56.374 --> 43:58.291
-RALPH: I just-- I get it--
-GLORY: No, you can't be here.

43:58.374 --> 44:00.124
-RALPH: I need to talk to you.
Please talk to me.
-GLORY: No.

44:00.207 --> 44:02.124
RALPH: Look, I should never have
arrested Terry the way I did--

44:02.207 --> 44:04.082
-Get your foot off my door.
-I did a lot of things wrong.

44:04.166 --> 44:05.249
Get your fucking foot
off my door.

44:05.333 --> 44:06.583
-Glory, please.
-I'm gonna get you arrested,

44:06.666 --> 44:07.957
-get it off.
-You need to hear me out.

44:08.041 --> 44:09.166
I need to what?

44:12.625 --> 44:13.625
Back the fuck up.

44:13.708 --> 44:15.291
RALPH: What if he didn't do it?

44:15.374 --> 44:16.541
He didn't do it!

44:16.625 --> 44:18.416
He didn't do it.

44:18.499 --> 44:20.249
He told you he didn't do it.

44:20.333 --> 44:22.916
The last words my husband spoke
were to you, and not to me.

44:22.999 --> 44:26.207
They were to you,
and he told you he didn't do it.

44:26.291 --> 44:28.916
So, what else do you need?
A note from God?

44:30.249 --> 44:31.625
If he didn't do it...

44:32.249 --> 44:33.291
someone else did.

44:35.750 --> 44:37.416
What if it happens again?

44:38.583 --> 44:40.999
Are you asking me for my help?

44:41.082 --> 44:42.374
-Yeah
-(GLORY SCOFFS)

44:43.708 --> 44:46.416
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

44:47.916 --> 44:50.499
Maybe you can help me with
a few things.

44:50.583 --> 44:51.708
RALPH: Okay.

44:54.583 --> 44:57.750
How am I supposed to get my kids
safely to school every day?

44:59.333 --> 45:01.583
How am I supposed to
explain to them

45:01.666 --> 45:03.374
why they no longer have friends?

45:05.291 --> 45:08.291
Why people are screaming curses
at our windows,

45:08.374 --> 45:10.625
and throwing shit
all over our porch,

45:10.708 --> 45:12.124
and even if we move...

45:13.625 --> 45:15.875
this whole goddamn thing

45:15.957 --> 45:17.750
is tattooed on our faces.

45:18.957 --> 45:20.124
What do I do with that?

45:25.333 --> 45:26.416
The only way...

45:28.124 --> 45:31.291
you're gonna get your life back
is by clearing Terry's name,

45:31.374 --> 45:32.791
and the only way to do that

45:32.875 --> 45:36.249
is to find whoever killed
Frankie Peterson.

45:36.333 --> 45:38.333
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

45:38.416 --> 45:40.124
Glory, to do that
I need your help.

45:42.708 --> 45:45.957
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

45:48.124 --> 45:50.625
♪ (EERIE MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

46:06.207 --> 46:09.708
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

46:16.791 --> 46:18.666
(STAIRS SQUEAKING)

46:42.041 --> 46:43.041
(GLORY SIGHS)

46:46.166 --> 46:47.708
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

46:48.999 --> 46:52.207
♪ (EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

47:15.708 --> 47:17.082
(BRAKES SQUEAK)

47:19.333 --> 47:21.416
You know, in Russia,
when Stalin had his goons

47:21.499 --> 47:23.082
drag people from their homes

47:23.166 --> 47:25.583
to be murdered
in some prison basement,

47:25.666 --> 47:27.166
you know how he topped that off?

47:27.249 --> 47:28.625
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

47:28.708 --> 47:30.625
He would send
the dead man's family a bill

47:30.708 --> 47:32.082
for the used bullet.

47:35.458 --> 47:38.291
You talking to Glory Maitland
for help...

47:38.374 --> 47:39.957
that's what this sounds like
to me.

47:40.999 --> 47:43.124
Yeah, I can see how you would
see it that way.

47:44.249 --> 47:46.957
If you think by talking to her

47:47.041 --> 47:49.750
you can in any way stop me from
filing a suit against you,

47:49.833 --> 47:52.708
or your department, Hayes,
or anyone else, you're wrong.

47:52.791 --> 47:54.541
Don't give a damn about
any of that.

48:09.791 --> 48:11.124
(WATER STOPS RUNNING)

48:11.207 --> 48:12.750
(RALPH SNIFFS)

48:12.833 --> 48:14.666
-(CLEARS THROAT)
-(OPENS DOOR)

48:22.999 --> 48:24.333
RALPH: Hey, Glory,
thank you very much

48:24.416 --> 48:26.791
for letting me into your house,
and, um, thank you for--

48:26.875 --> 48:28.041
HOWARD: Enough.

48:28.124 --> 48:30.750
You told Mrs. Maitland
you wanted to talk to her.

48:30.833 --> 48:32.458
-Go.
-"Needed,"

48:32.541 --> 48:33.833
is what he said. "Needed."

48:33.916 --> 48:36.416
What do you need
to talk to her about?

48:36.916 --> 48:38.541
RALPH: Um...

48:38.625 --> 48:42.166
There's some new information
that has come my way.

48:42.750 --> 48:44.124
Now...

48:44.207 --> 48:48.207
in and of itself it may be
inconsequential, but--

48:48.291 --> 48:49.333
Punch line?

48:51.333 --> 48:54.833
Turns out that the van that was
used to abduct the Peterson boy

48:54.916 --> 48:58.333
was stolen in New York
by a 12-year-old kid.

48:58.416 --> 49:01.291
This was the first of three
vehicles he stole,

49:01.374 --> 49:04.249
and he wound up in Chattanooga,
which is where he was caught,

49:04.333 --> 49:05.541
but, um... May I?

49:09.249 --> 49:13.999
But he dumped that van
in Dayton on March 6th.

49:14.458 --> 49:15.499
What of it?

49:16.458 --> 49:17.499
Glory...

49:18.875 --> 49:20.750
that's when you
and your family were there.

49:20.833 --> 49:22.833
You're still trying to put this
on Terry?

49:22.916 --> 49:23.957
No! No, no.

49:24.041 --> 49:25.791
-That's not what this about--
-This is done.

49:25.875 --> 49:26.957
Um, please,

49:27.041 --> 49:28.875
just hear me out.
I-- Look, please.

49:28.957 --> 49:31.249
I know that you and your family
flew both ways.

49:31.333 --> 49:33.666
That's not in question,

49:33.750 --> 49:36.207
and Terry himself told me
he never saw the van,

49:36.291 --> 49:38.625
let alone stole it.
I wanna believe that,

49:38.708 --> 49:41.124
we have his fingerprints
all over the goddamn thing,

49:41.207 --> 49:42.333
but I want to.

49:42.416 --> 49:44.124
What's the punch line?

49:44.207 --> 49:45.875
There is none! But...

49:48.791 --> 49:50.416
do you see how strange this is?

49:51.207 --> 49:53.041
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

49:53.124 --> 49:54.207
RALPH: Dayton...

49:55.374 --> 49:57.124
to Cherokee City,

49:57.207 --> 49:59.625
I mean, that's not exactly
Paris to London.

49:59.708 --> 50:01.333
It's as if this van just...

50:03.625 --> 50:04.708
followed you home.

50:05.374 --> 50:06.541
Maybe it was haunted.

50:06.625 --> 50:09.166
Yeah, my mother the car.

50:09.249 --> 50:11.249
Please just bear with me for
a moment here.

50:13.166 --> 50:15.708
Why Dayton for
a family vacation?

50:15.791 --> 50:17.416
Why not go to Orlando or--

50:17.499 --> 50:21.708
Because Terry's father is
in Dayton, in a senior center,

50:21.791 --> 50:23.458
but Terry's the only one
who sees him

50:23.541 --> 50:26.541
because the man has dementia,
and tends to be violent.

50:26.625 --> 50:27.833
RALPH: Okay.

50:27.916 --> 50:31.750
So, this vacation, when Terry
was off visiting his father,

50:31.833 --> 50:33.291
what did you and the girls do?

50:33.374 --> 50:35.333
He was only gone
a few hours a day.

50:35.416 --> 50:38.249
We stayed in the hotel pool,
we went to the mall,

50:38.666 --> 50:40.041
a movie.

50:40.124 --> 50:42.791
RALPH: When he came back,
did you ever go out to eat?

50:44.583 --> 50:45.708
Once or twice.

50:45.791 --> 50:48.416
You ever go to a place called
Big Daddy's Hangry BBQ?

50:50.124 --> 50:51.791
Big Daddy's Hangry BBQ?

50:51.875 --> 50:53.791
RALPH: BBQ restaurant,
has a pig logo.

50:55.333 --> 50:57.124
I'd like this to be done.

50:57.207 --> 50:59.541
No, please, just one more.

50:59.625 --> 51:04.207
Did anything out of the ordinary
happen while you were in Dayton?

51:04.291 --> 51:07.416
Did one of the girls go missing
for a short while?

51:07.499 --> 51:10.082
Did Terry say that he'd met up
with an old friend?

51:10.166 --> 51:11.791
-Did you--
-Nothing happened!

51:12.625 --> 51:14.541
Terry visited his dad,

51:14.625 --> 51:16.708
we hung out, we came home,

51:16.791 --> 51:18.625
we didn't eat at a restaurant
called

51:18.708 --> 51:21.791
Big Daddy's Hangry BBQ,
and he didn't steal the van.

51:23.791 --> 51:24.791
Goodnight.

51:25.499 --> 51:26.957
MAYA: Daddy got a cut.

51:34.416 --> 51:35.458
(DOOR CREAKS)

51:35.541 --> 51:37.291
Hey, love,
what are you doing down here?

51:37.374 --> 51:39.458
Jessa was yelling at her
nightmare and woke me up.

51:39.541 --> 51:41.207
You should give her Benadryl
next time.

51:41.291 --> 51:42.416
GLORY: Come, I'll take you up.

51:42.499 --> 51:44.499
(FOOTSTEPS ON STAIRS)

51:44.583 --> 51:45.875
(STAIRS CREAK)

51:45.957 --> 51:47.333
GLORY: Come on, let's go.

51:49.999 --> 51:51.833
Are you the man that killed
my father?

51:56.249 --> 51:59.499
No, um-- No, Maya, I'm not,
but I am...

52:00.999 --> 52:04.708
I made some terrible mistakes
with him and, um,

52:05.708 --> 52:08.416
uh, I'm gonna live
with those mistakes

52:08.499 --> 52:09.708
for the rest of my life.

52:12.249 --> 52:13.333
GLORY: Let's go.

52:15.166 --> 52:16.124
Hey, Maya,

52:16.207 --> 52:18.124
can I just ask you,
before you go upstairs,

52:18.207 --> 52:20.082
can I just ask you to tell me
about...

52:20.999 --> 52:22.666
tell me about your dad's cut?

52:25.791 --> 52:27.333
He got it visiting Grandpa.

52:29.166 --> 52:31.875
Okay, wh--
why do you remember that?

52:34.541 --> 52:35.708
Because...

52:35.791 --> 52:38.041
he said he'd got it
from a nurse...

52:39.166 --> 52:40.374
but the nurse was a man.

52:43.708 --> 52:46.041
Yeah, yeah, sometimes nurses
can be men.

52:47.041 --> 52:48.708
Did he tell you how he got it?

52:50.916 --> 52:53.999
He said he was walking
in a hallway,

52:54.082 --> 52:56.625
he bumped into the nurse
on a wet floor,

52:58.666 --> 53:01.249
he grabbed the nurse's hand
as he fell down,

53:01.333 --> 53:03.082
and when he got back up he...

53:04.166 --> 53:06.082
saw he'd got a cut on his wrist.

53:07.249 --> 53:09.249
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

53:11.458 --> 53:12.791
Mom...

53:12.875 --> 53:14.916
there was a pig restaurant...

53:15.708 --> 53:17.541
in the mall, near our hotel.

53:18.708 --> 53:21.791
Jessa saw the sign for it when
we were shopping there,

53:22.750 --> 53:23.750
remember?

53:25.583 --> 53:26.750
I don't remember.

53:26.833 --> 53:27.875
Let's go to bed.

53:27.957 --> 53:29.750
-RALPH: Glory.
-GLORY: (CLEARS THROAT) Come on.

53:29.833 --> 53:32.207
RALPH: Hey, Glory,
do you remember this cut?

53:32.291 --> 53:34.041
It was a cut,

53:34.124 --> 53:36.291
he put something on it,
and that was it.

53:37.625 --> 53:38.791
Goodnight!

53:43.625 --> 53:45.291
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

54:15.666 --> 54:16.999
(FOOTSTEPS)

54:23.207 --> 54:25.708
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

54:38.207 --> 54:40.999
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

57:15.333 --> 57:17.082
(SIRENS WAILING)

57:17.374 --> 57:18.999
MAN:
We gotta retrace the steps...

57:19.207 --> 57:21.499
Find where this whole
horror show started.

57:24.333 --> 57:26.207
HOWIE GOLD:
How about sending Holly Gibney?

57:26.833 --> 57:28.916
Can we get her on this?
There's nobody better.

57:29.541 --> 57:32.166
All these contradicting videos
and forensics.

57:32.416 --> 57:33.750
Sounds like there's
a connection.

57:33.833 --> 57:34.833
(THUNDER CLASPS)

57:34.916 --> 57:36.875
Do you see how strange this is?

57:40.499 --> 57:42.625
You need to tell me
what this is about, Holly.

57:42.708 --> 57:44.708
I'm afraid nobody's going
to believe me.

57:46.875 --> 57:47.999
He didn't do it.

57:48.374 --> 57:51.957
A human being cannot be
in two realities

57:52.041 --> 57:53.207
at the same time.

57:54.458 --> 57:57.583
I have no, um, tolerance,
for the unexplainable.

57:57.999 --> 57:58.916
(SCREAMING)

57:59.583 --> 58:02.166
HOLLY GIBNEY:
If you can't get yourself
to really believe in this,

58:02.875 --> 58:04.583
you're a danger
to everyone else.

58:08.583 --> 58:09.999
(RAT SCURRYING)

58:11.583 --> 58:12.625
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

58:12.708 --> 58:13.791
♪ (MUSIC STOPS) ♪

58:14.249 --> 58:15.833
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

58:15.916 --> 58:18.207
I think you should drop
the investigation.

58:19.583 --> 58:20.374
If you don't,

58:20.750 --> 58:22.666
I feel like something very bad
is gonna happen.

58:24.833 --> 58:26.708
RALPH: Something bad's
already happened.

58:26.791 --> 58:28.374
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

58:29.458 --> 58:30.416
(SCREAMS)

58:30.666 --> 58:31.666
♪ (MUSIC STOPS) ♪

58:31.750 --> 58:33.082
JEANNIE ANDERSON: He's here.

58:34.291 --> 58:36.916
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪
